-- OFT’s Chief Economist to Leave Regulator for University Post
-- B y   A o i f e   W h i t e
-- 2013-01-18T16:52:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-18/oft-s-chief-economist-to-leave-regulator-for-university-post.html
The  Office of Fair Trading ’s chief
economist, Amelia Fletcher, will leave the regulator to become a
university professor.  Frank Shepherd, a spokesman for the London-based antitrust
agency, said in a telephone interview that Fletcher would take
up a post at the Norwich Business School at the University of
East Anglia in April. The university announced the appointment
in a  statement  on its website earlier today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aoife White in Brussels at 
 awhite62@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Anthony Aarons at   aaarons@bloomberg.net . 